content:
Add a Number to a Call Center Directory

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience, Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
Manage Call Centers

From Setup, enter Directory Numbers in the Quick Find box. Click Edit or New.

In the Name field, enter a label that identifies the additional directory number.
In the Phone field, enter the phone number, including any international country codes.
In the Call Center field, select the call center directory to which you want to add the new directory number.
In the Description field, optionally enter text that provides further information about the additional directory number.

Click Save or Save & New.
title: Adding Numbers to Call Center Directories in Salesforce
